Inner transformation
Many in the spiritual communitty talk about the dark night of
the soul, as I went trough my second dark night of the soul
very recently I started to pay more attention to understand it
in a wordly but still subjective manner.
I see the dark night as a nervous system breakdown and an
identitty crisis of who you used to be as you continue to grow
out of your survival personalitties, your nervous system goes
into a fight, flight or freeze (where the last one I am most
familiar with subdivides to either excessive anger or dissocia-
tion where you leave your body as a dear in distress about to
be eaten, you loose any sense of your personalitty in the
process of discontinual stress response) for reconciliation
and transforming the trauma I would suggest cleansing the
mind - brain harmonisation, somatic exersises to bring your
heart back into play to guide you back to your truth, the self
that arises and guides without the many personalitties com-
menting on others and yourself and in the process removing
dopamine as well, all that is stimulating to find a way to brin you
back into your body, into the now and feeling safe.
